CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1964, pg. 12, reads: "Entertained - Some of the youngsters who entertained Cornell Hawkins Bell of Philadelphia, nephew of Miss Maude Y. Hawkins, who has been spending the summer in Pittsburgh. Left to right: Carol Finch, Joseph Finch Jr., Cornell H. Bell, the honoree, and Lynda Branch.  Kneeling in foreground is Susan Finch, holding the dog, Petit Garcon D'Argent. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Carol Finch, Joseph Finch Jr., Cornell H. Bell, and Lynda Branch, with Susan Finch kneeling in the foreground with dog "Petit Garcon D'Argent, " posed in yard, possibly of Maude Y. Hawkins
